[A map of SBV in Germany as of 3 Feb 2012 is available at http://www.fli.bund.de/fileadmin/dam_uploads/tierseuchen/Schmallenberg_Virus/Karten/Map_Schmallenberg_20120203.jpg.

A map of SBV in the Netherlands, as of 3 Feb 2012, is available at http://www.vwa.nl/txmpub/files/?p_file_id=2201854; the Dutch table on reporting, tested, confirmed, not confirmed, and under-examination farms, according to species, is available at
http://www.vwa.nl/txmpub/files/?p_file_id=2201855.
The Netherlands submitted its 3rd SBV follow-up report to OIE with map on 31 Jan 2012; available at
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=event_summary&reportid=11447.

The Belgian map of SBV, as of 1 Feb 2012 is available at http://www.afsca.be/_pictures/users/Schmallenberg_20120201b_000.jpg;
In total, as of 1 Feb 2012, 349 animal farms in Belgium have been examined for SBV, of which 80 were found (PCR) positive; this included 238 cattle farms (4 positive), 104 sheep farms (75 positive) and 7 goat farms (1 positive).

France submitted to the OIE its 1st report on SBV on 31 Jan 2012. The report, covering 29 outbreaks, all in sheep, with an interactive map, is available at http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=11568.

It will be interesting to note if cows which were observed/recorded as suffering from the (mild) clinical disease, attributed to SBV, which was seen during Aug-Oct 2011 in Germany and Netherlands, have given or will give birth to malformed offspring, and if some of them seem to have lost their foeti.

EU's Standing Committee on the Food Chain and Animal Health - SCFCAH (Section Animal Health and Welfare) is to convene on Tue, 7 Feb 2012 in Brussels for its monthly 2-day meeting. The 1st issue on the agenda (Section A) will be: "Schmallenberg virus: review of the epidemiological situation and exchange of views on working document SANCO/7012/2012". In view of the dimensions of the emerging epizootic and the reported involvement of 5 member states (Belgium, France, Germany, Netherlands and UK), significant surveillance and research activities are expected to be discussed and, hopefully, approved and budgetted. The report of the previous meeting (1-12 Jan 2012), the working document mentioned and the outcome of the discussions, as well as the individual presentations of the countries involved, are anticipated with interest. - Mod.AS.]
